properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 15 at 3:00AM CST until January 15 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...LIGHT SNOW TODAY...

.Light snow is expected over the Northland early this morning
through this afternoon as a trough of low pressure moves eastward
across the region. The greatest snow amounts will stretch from
central Minnesota east into northwest Wisconsin. A swath of 2 to
5 inches of snow is forecast for the advisory area. Lake
enhancement to the snow is expected along the South Shore of Lake
Superior which will yield 3 to 5 inches for the northern tier of
zones, with 2 to 4 inches for the southern tier. An initial wave
of light snow will lift northeastward across east- central
Minnesota and northwest Wisconsin early this morning. The main
body of snow will approach from the west later this morning and
will depart to the east this afternoon and evening. The snow may
make conditions slippery for the morning and evening commutes.

* WHAT...Snow with total accumulation of 2 to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Sawyer, Price, Iron, Burnett, Washburn, Douglas,
Bayfield and Ashland Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands
of the Red Cliff Band and the Bad River Reservation.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions, including during
the morning and evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road
conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
